================================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================================

This project incorporates or references components from the following
upstream projects. Their licenses and notices are preserved and apply to the
corresponding portions of this work.

1. stellar/soroban-examples
   - Source: https://github.com/stellar/soroban-examples
   - Pinned commit: 7b168174ae1268dab91a0190d80a94ab7ff41b59
   - License: Apache-2.0 at the repository root. The `privacy-pools`
     subtree additionally carries its own MIT license; copied files retain
     that notice.
   - Usage: Reference implementation for Groth16 BLS12-381 verifier
     (`groth16_verifier`) and the privacy-pools commitments/nullifier design
     that ZK-Quorum adapts. The two-arity Poseidon helper
     (`poseidon255.circom`) and the Merkle gadgets are derived from
     `spike/soroban-examples/circuits`; they are not imported from circomlib.

2. iden3/circom
   - Source: https://github.com/iden3/circom
   - Pinned version: 2.2.3
   - License: GPL-3.0 (upstream). The compiled binary is downloaded by
     `scripts/bootstrap/bootstrap.sh` for the host platform.
   - Usage: Circuit compiler.

3. iden3/snarkjs
   - Source: https://github.com/iden3/snarkjs
   - Pinned version: 0.7.6 (exact, no caret range)
   - License: GPL-3.0 (upstream).
   - Usage: Groth16 prover/verifier for BLS12-381 and Phase 2 contribution
     tooling.

The ZK-Quorum product code under `contracts/`, `crates/`, `circuits/`,
`apps/`, `services/`, and `tools/` is licensed under MIT as written above,
except where individual files declare a different upstream license header;
those upstream headers govern their respective files.
